# Income Insurance Premium Revenue Gross Of Ceded Amount

## identifier
de14129

## type
float

## definition
This is the value, during the relevant period, for the premium payable by the policyholder, which is net of discounts and promotions, but gross of any commissions and/or fees taken by intermediaries. The premium revenues must be gross of any reinsurance arrangements whereby premium is ceded to a reinsurer. This is calculated in accordance with the relevant accounting standard.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=credit
- name=Income.Insurance.PremiumRevenueGrossOfCeded.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpr/bafpr3.02.21
- period=duration
